cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.LO, cs.IT, cs.CC

Reasoning: 
1. cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with automata-theoretic characterization of piecewise-testable languages and shuffle products, which are core topics in formal languages and automata theory.
2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also a likely category as the paper discusses acyclic automata, which are a type of data structure used in automata theory.
3. cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is a possible category as the paper deals with language complexity and provides bounds on the piecewise complexity of shuffle products.
4. cs.IT (Information Theory) is a possible category as the paper discusses the properties of finite languages and their shuffle products, which are related to information theory.
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possible category as the paper discusses the complexity of piecewise-testable languages and provides bounds on their piecewise complexity.
